description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an exceptional Staff Nurse to join our dedicated multi professional team on our &lt;strong&gt;Inpatient Unit&lt;/strong&gt; providing symptom management and complex end of life care to our patients living with a life limiting condition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This important role will be responsible for the assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of evidence based patient care and for providing invaluable support to the patient’s family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is desirable but not essential that applicants have HEA 3038, Mentorship in practice or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications from experienced, return to practice or newly qualified nurses are welcomed. A comprehensive induction will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please see attachements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Only candidates selected for interview will be contacted. Previous applicants in the last 12 months need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woodlands Hospice Charitable Trust - Charity number 1048934&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse - Full Time 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Part time hours will be considered)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Scale £24,907- £30,615 pro rata, per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;plus enhanced rates for nights/weekends&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contract of employment is with Woodlands Hospice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;however the pay scale mirrors NHS Agenda for Change Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
